The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Gold for Sodhi 
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Gold for Sodhi 
                      
	New Delhi: Trap shooter Ronjon Sodhi registered his name in the record books and became the first Indian to win a gold medal in the double trap event at the shooting world cup in Belgrade on Wednesday.         
	Sodhi fired a score of 194 (147+47) to equal the world record set by D.I. Spigno of Italy in the 1999 world championship in shotgun events. (PTI)                                                                                                                          
